<h2 id="head-d44d13b657ebda3d6bb3c656050854bf70021268">Where can I try out TomeNet? Does it have a server running?</h2>
<p>
Simon: I couldn't find any evidence of a <a class="nonexistent" href="./TomeNet">TomeNet</a> server active. But there are people complaining about things in the tomeNet forum, so maybe it existed but is now down?? 
</p>

    <ul>

 <a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a>: The europe server where active a couple months ago, when I used to play tomenet. <p>
 <a class="nonexistent" href="./FiZz">FiZz</a>: you have to connect on europe server at europe.tomenet.net or tomenet.librenet.net as the meta server is still down 
</p>

    </ul>


<p>
Simon: <a class="nonexistent" href="./TomeNet">TomeNet</a> FAQ and *JUICY SPOILERS* <a href=".www.c-blue.de/rogue/TomeNET-Guide.txt">http://www.c-blue.de/rogue/TomeNET-Guide.txt</a> still couldn't figure out how to install the client, if there are tomeNet servers available, etc. 
</p>
<p>
The spoilers aren't 100% what happens in tome, but knowing the slays exact multipliers and such was a godsend. Spoiler-writers look here! 
</p>

    <ul>

 <a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a>: Download it, unzip, run the bat for europe ... at least that's what I remember from it. 
    </ul>


<h2 id="head-855388a005ace15316575235882b37dd276fb1b4">What are the differences with ToME?</h2>
<p>
Simon: according to the forums... 
</p>
<p>
-The choice between immortal and regular characters. An immortal has the cheat death activated but can't give items to a mortal player. 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 <a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a>: They have other penalities as well. There are several types of characters... From hardcore (whatever the name was, one life I think)  to immortal characters. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
-Wilderness travel doesn't exist and walking has to be done "by hand" all the way (this sounds unlikely to be true, I have to see it to believe it!) 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 <a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a>: Last time I checked it was true. Mostly because walking is done in real time. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
-No fee was mentionned anywhere, so this is PROBABLY a free thing too. I don't think <a href="./DarkGod">DarkGod</a> would have it any other way (correct me if I'm wrong, was it <a href="./DarkGod">DarkGod</a> who made ToME?). 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 <a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a>: It is free. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
-They have no alchemists or possessors, but mimics are more advanced. 
</p>
<p>
-The skill tree has more bugs and incosistencies (and skills NO ONE uses) than tome. 
</p>
<p>
-You can form a party if everyone in it is no more than 7 levels apart, and share XP. Wooo-hoo! 
</p>
<p>
-Thunderlords can consume special gems to obtain temporary powers, and race-specific bonuses and penalities are much more common and nontrivial than in tome. 
</p>
<p>
-You can play a "fruit bat". (-; 
</p>
